description: This file defines a test case class X32libTest for verifying whether a binary file is an x86-64 ELF32 file. It utilizes oeqa framework components to manage the test setup and dependencies, and performs shell commands to analyze binary headers.

classes.name: X32libTest
classes.description: A test case class that checks if a copied binary is a valid X86-64 ELF32 binary.

methods.name: test_x32_file(self)
methods.description: Test method that copies /bin/ls to a temporary location, then verifies it is an ELF32 binary for x86-64 architecture using readelf output.
